# OpenAI Codex Provider (chatgpt.com/backend-api/codex/responses)

The Codex provider uses the **Responses API** format, NOT Chat Completions. All requests go through `_adapt_to_codex_responses()` in `ghost_providers.py`.

## Accepted Parameters

| Parameter       | Accepted | Notes |
|----------------|----------|-------|
| `model`        | Yes      | Strip provider prefix (`openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex` → `gpt-5.3-codex`) |
| `input`        | Yes      | Converted from `messages` — user/assistant/tool messages become input items |
| `instructions` | Yes      | Converted from system/developer messages. Defaults to fallback if empty |
| `tools`        | Yes      | Converted from OpenAI function format to Responses API format |
| `tool_choice`  | Yes      | **Must be passed through** — `"auto"`, `"required"`, `"none"` |
| `store`        | Yes      | Always `false` (required by Codex backend) |
| `stream`       | Yes      | Always `true` (required by Codex backend) |

## Rejected Parameters (will return HTTP 400)

| Parameter           | Error |
|---------------------|-------|
| `temperature`       | `Unsupported parameter: temperature` |
| `max_tokens`        | Unsupported (Chat Completions param) |
| `max_output_tokens` | `Unsupported parameter: max_output_tokens` |

**Never add these to the adapted Codex payload.** The Codex backend is stricter than the standard OpenAI Responses API.

## Critical: tool_choice Must Be Forwarded

Without `tool_choice`, the Codex model may respond with text claiming it completed a task **without actually calling any tools**. This causes the model to hallucinate actions (e.g., "I updated the file" when no `file_write` was called).

The tool loop in `ghost_loop.py` sets `tool_choice` on every step:
- Step 0 with `force_tool=True`: `"required"`
- All other steps: `"auto"`

The adapter **must** include this in the Codex payload.

## Message Format Conversion

| Chat Completions | Codex Responses API |
|-----------------|---------------------|
| `messages[role=system]` | `instructions` (string, concatenated) |
| `messages[role=user]` | `input` item `{type: "message", role: "user"}` |
| `messages[role=assistant]` with `tool_calls` | `input` items `{type: "function_call", call_id, name, arguments}` |
| `messages[role=tool]` | `input` item `{type: "function_call_output", call_id, output}` |

## Tool Schema Validation

The Codex API enforces **strict JSON Schema**. All `array` type parameters must have an `items` field. The `_fix_array_schemas()` utility handles this automatically, but new tool definitions should include `items` from the start.

## Authentication

- Uses OAuth token from `ghost_oauth.ensure_fresh_token()`
- Requires `ChatGPT-Account-Id` header from the auth profile
- Token is a ChatGPT Plus subscription token, NOT an OpenAI API key

## Response Handling

Responses are **SSE streamed**. Use `parse_codex_sse_response()` to consume the stream and extract the `response.completed` event. Then `_adapt_from_codex_responses()` converts `output` items back to Chat Completions `choices` format.
